import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name_length'] = data['name'].apply(len)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='name_length', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['name_length'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by length?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['country'])
    chart = sns.countplot(x='country', data=data, order=data['country'].value_counts().index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.set_xlabel('Country')
    chart.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
